data.name: button1.ToolTip
data.value: Click to add forlder to the list

data.name: textBox_extensions.ToolTip
data.value: Enter extensions here, use ',' to split.

data.name: checkBox_includeSubFolders.ToolTip
data.value: If enabled, the program will search inside all folders of the folders in the list including the sub folders (the folders inside the folders)

data.name: checkBox_matchCase.ToolTip
data.value: Use match case in search (case sensetive...)

data.name: checkBox_matchWord.ToolTip
data.value: Use match word in search (Use this for MAME detects.)

data.name: checkBox_deleteOldDetected.Text
data.value: Clear old detect files from rom (i.e. clear old images, info files...). No file will be deleted, only the detect info.

data.name: checkBox_deleteOldDetected.ToolTip
data.value: Clear the old related files associated with roms for this information container.

data.name: checkBox_oneFilePerRom.ToolTip
data.value: This will force to assign only one detected file to matched rom even the rom matched more than one file.

data.name: checkBox_dontAllowMoreThanOneFile.Text
data.value: Don't assign same file to more than one rom.

data.name: checkBox_dontAllowMoreThanOneFile.ToolTip
data.value:
If enabled, once a file detected and matched a rom, this file will be removed from the detected files list. This mean (for example) if we have 2 roms and one file match the both roms, the first rom will take the file and then detected file removed and won't be used again.
This option may increase detection speed.

data.name: button5.ToolTip
data.value: Click to reset the extensions to defaults.

data.name: checkBox_useRomNameInstead.Text
data.value: &Use rom name instead of rom file name

data.name: checkBox_useRomNameInstead.ToolTip
data.value: The search engine look for matched files using the rom file name, enable this if you want to use rom name instead.

data.name: checkBox_reverse.ToolTip
data.value:
If enabled, the search files array will be sorted Z to A Otherwise arrays will be sorted normally A to Z (default)
This may help detect more files in some cases.

data.name: radioButton_searchmode_rominfile.ToolTip
data.value: Force the search mode: rom in file which means the rom name/filename searched inside the file name.

data.name: radioButton_searchmode_fileinrom.ToolTip
data.value: Force the search mode: file in rom which means the file name searched inside the rom name/filename.

data.name: radioButton_startWith.ToolTip
data.value: Use start with type when searching text. i.e. the target name should start with search name.

data.name: radioButton_endwith.ToolTip
data.value: Use end with type when searching text. i.e. the target name should ends with search name.

data.name: radioButton_contains.ToolTip
data.value: Use contains type when searching text. i.e. the target name should contain search name anywhere.

data.name: checkBox_removeSymbols.ToolTip
data.value: Remove symbols from rom file names i.e. [U], [E], [!]....

data.name: checkBox_remove_specified_symbols.Text
data.value: Remove these specified symbols or words (split with ','):

data.name: checkBox_remove_specified_symbols.ToolTip
data.value: If set. EO will remove the symboles entered in the text box when comparing.

data.name: button6.ToolTip
data.value: Click to reset the extensions to defaults.

data.name: radioButton_folder_folder.ToolTip
data.value: In this mode, EO will repeat the search process folder by folder, as arranged in the list. This mode is slower since it will repeat the process... But the detected files will be ordered as the list, for example, file 1 from folder 1 will be the first image for a game, the second image will be file 2 from from folder 2.... etc

data.name: radioButton_mode_default.ToolTip
data.value: In this mode, EO will collect all the files from all the folders listed randomlly then starting the comparing process. This is faster, but detected files may not in order as the in the list. For example, file 1 from folder 2 will be the first image for a game, the second image will be file 2 from from folder 5.... etc
